*Environment*

* _Eucalyptus Version_
{{4.4.0-0.25741.120.20170118git85b6870.el7}}
* _Setup_
Federated setup with two Eucalyptus VPC clouds
** [hspencer-240-maint-4.4|http://jenkins.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com/job/Quick%20Launch%20Maint_4.4/240/]
** [hspencer-243-maint-4.4|http://jenkins.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com/job/Quick%20Launch%20Maint_4.4/243/]
{code}
[root@d-02 ~]# euca-describe-regions
REGION	drake	http://ec2.d-14.autoqa.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com:8773/
REGION	future	http://ec2.c-29.autoqa.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com:8773/

[root@c-25 ~]# euca-describe-availability-zones

AVAILABILITYZONE	evol	available

fields.summary: ELB responds with 503 with an InService state instance

comments.body: The issue couldn't be reproduced on a cloud with sufficient amount of RAM on the CLC and UFS.  Since the cloud that this issue was discovered had signs of heavy swapping, this seems to have contributed to this behavior.  Therefore, closing the ticket.
